  "text": "Wolthuis and colleagues studied tidal volume use in three adult ICUs in the Netherlands to determine the effect of feedback and education concerning the use of lung protective MV. They have found that education did improve physician compliance in the use of lung protective ventilatory strategies, with a tidal volume decline within 6 months after intervention from 9.8 ml/kg ± 2.0 at baseline to 8.1 ±1.7 ml/ kg. [CITATION_1] The feedback and education program focused on lungprotective MV, with an emphasis on adjusting tidal volumes to predicted body weight (PBW).",
